place_description: Counter-serve bakery/cafe chain serving sandwiches, salads & more, known for its bread & free WiFi.

reviews_data.review_text: I have gone to this location many times and always get great service. One of my favorite item on the menu is the Spicy Fiesta Chicken sandwich which I highly recommend. Angel the manager is very knowledgeable about the items on the menu and always nice and courteous.
Great food but over priced.

Haven't been to Panerai Bread in ages. Tried one of the new salads. There was nothing wrong with it. I just didn't like it. Most definitely, I will go back and try another one. Customer service was good. Price reasonable.
Great restaurant,  great prices!!

I love coming to this Panera. The Manager Angel is always so nice and polite. He always go the extra mile when my family and I visit. It's so refreshing to see people who truly love and enjoy what they do.

Such a warm and friendly atmosphere. One of my favorite lunch spots for an amazing Mediterranean salad! Staff is helpful. Once they got my order wrong, but they were SO accommodating and the manager got it corrected right away. Everyone can make an error, but how they correct it can mean a lot these days. I was really appreciative of the kind way they handled the issue, even during a busy time in the restaurant.
The food was delicious. My mom was sick, so I bought her a bowl of chicken noodle soup. She said it made her feel much better. The bowl size for soup is great and satisfying.
Food was great and the bakery especially did a good job with there bread. Service was amazing, great workers here.
Good sandwich.
Bom atendimento
I ordered a rapid pickup order last minute for lunch and it was ready in less than the pickup time and it was accurate and fresh. Customer service was friendly and inviting.
Nice staff, quiet place to eat yummy good! Much better than other fast food options!
Everywhere was very dirty, and the greens of my salad were not fresh.don't come here

Honestly the best service we've ever had at a Panera bread, such quality and efficiency! Employees are so respectful and patient, and one kind gentleman even helped me carry our food out to the table and brought water for our dog :) We were impressed with the amazing hospitality!!
Love their soups, sandwiches, bagels, and pastries

We have eaten here many times.  We stopped for dinner tonight and it was empty.  We got a very friendly cashier who was so helpful.  We ordered our food and waited to be called to pick it up.  We got hot sandwiches and soup which were really good.  The only reason for 4 stars is because dirty dishes were piling up at the drop off area.

Why does the Caesar salad with chicken not come with chicken. Three times I've ordered for delivery and had no chicken.

No hot water for tea. I bet the coffee is cold as well. Poorly managed location.
Good was good
Remi was excellent and very efficient cashier. Take notice Matthews! First class
Chai latte was great! Pick up name was wrong.
We love Paneras breads and pick 2 meals. Always a go-to for us.
Nice and clean, fantastic soup and grilled cheese!!
My realtor, Nancy Jarrell, took me out to lunch after my house closed at signing.
Excelent place

This Panera needs designated people to clean after each customer leaves. I had to wipe down my table and seat cushions for my friend and I before we could sit down at the table. Most of the table and chairs were dirty. It was crumbs everywhere. It seemed to be a lot of staff behind the counter but no one on the floor. I won't be returning. Please visit the new Panera on 49. A perfect example of what a Panera should look like.

There was a man named Hector that works at the panera bread in Matthews. He was VERRRRRY rude to me and my 5 year old cousine, cussing us out and telling us he was going to "tickle us". While saying all of these thing he kept signaling me to come outside and fight me. Please do not come here unless you want a very bad food experience.  1 star

At this location they always get my order right, have world class customer service always.  Today the manager helped me with an online order where I made a mistake.  I thank him for excellent customer service!

Got the pick 2 for lunch - ham sandwich and broccoli cheddar soup which was good but the best part was I got a baker's dozen bagels of cinnamon crunch and multi grain which is an impossible feat in the nearby stores
My favorite Panera Bread. I go almost every day  Love  the staff. Being a part of the unlimited sips and rewards clubs makes the experience much more rewarding.
Always trashed. Overcrowded loud atmosphere.

Was served by a moon-faced boy named Nick who abruptly walked away from me in the middle of my order and walked to the other end of the store to help some other random man find the salt and pepper. They both couldn't wait one more minute?? All I wanted was a coffee and a muffin for christ's sake. Will definitely be switching back to using the kiosks, even though i'm SO bad at remembering to ring up my drinks when I use those  :) :)

Food was great as always! The atmosphere however was HORRIBLE. It was freezing in the dining room!  I hate to say that will keep us from returning! The people beside us asked staff to turn the air-conditioning off twice as did we. They went to their car and got blankets for the elderly couple with them just so tgey could stay and eat their meal.  It was also in t h e mid 60s outside so it was not a hot day at all.  We were totally ignored ALL OF US in our requests. My husband called the Matthews Store the next day to make the manager aware and was once again ignored! We won't   be back again!
I order ahead and food is fresh and ready when I arrive. When ordering in the store, good options and also fresh. Only thing I would like is not an option for the location and that's a drive thru.
The food and service is very good throughy enjoy it .

There is a young lady there name Weng. She helped me with an order that I made online supposed to pick up in another location, the cashier was about to charge me again for a new order but she stood up and saw my frustration and helped me to switch my order in this location. Sweet girl. God bless her.
They portion of the food here in this location were much lower than other Panera Breads that I have been too. I will never come to this location again.

Just left this Panera location and my family and I were at the kiosk placing our order and I happen to notice a baker using his cell phone and then he proceeded to roll the dough.  Didn't wash his hands, proceeded to pick the phone back up and touch the dough again.

I was immediately turned off and informed the manager and he gave a lack luster response and said he isn't "required" to wear gloves!  Okay, great but he shouldn't even have his phone out while working with food.

Needless to say, we were disgusted and left.
Good

Food portions on the sandwiches were pathetic for the price.  2 sandwiches, 2 drinks, 2 soups and total was $46.  It's one thing to pay that if the food is spot on with good portions but seriously paid for expensive bread.  Soup was ok and front desk cashier was nice.  Definitely wouldn't eat at another Panera because I would go broke and still be hungry!
Baguette bomb
Really poor internet.
One of my favorite Panera locations, super efficient service (which can't be said about every location). They stay on top of coffee, gets replaced without me having to tell them they ran out.
Delicious salad and amazing service from the lovely cashier Elle!

Just was there Sunday night at 6:11 pm June 25 2023.  Besides the service being very slow at the drive thru, we ordered 1/2 poppy seed strawberry salad and two cups of broccoli cheddar cheese.  When we arrived home, we were missing 3 French bag sides and  the poppy seed dressing.

Not being familiar with the area after being gone for a very long time, and dealing with the navigation in the car, I finally found this place. However, it was worth it! We got the Asian Crunch and Chicken Fuji Apple Salads. They were delicious. Even at lunchtime, very fast service. Highly recommend both of these salads.
Great place! Friendly staff and clean environment.
Great food, great service!
Food was good!

they kinda move slow to do mobile orders depending on the day. sometimes it says ready on the app and im still waiting 10/15 minutes after. its also irritating when they fill up the drink for u bc i dnt want a full cup of ice after i paid $5 for a drink.

Great Food and a Cozy atmosphere... The back-line workers were a bunch of snobby. Please teach your workers in the kitchen to show love that way it can be instilled into the food... This is Panera Bread for heaven's sake. The only person I saw with a Great Smile and Polite Attitude and was working as Cashier and Cleaning and Sweeping was the Young Man yesterday at 11am that took my order and I sat in Panera and are my food and watched for an hour ( Panera Bread ) Give that Young Man a Raise and learn from his Kindness. You'll never know when I the Truth Seeker is in your place of business

It was wonderful I just left there the beautiful young lady got order wrong and they fix me another with no problem and let me take other sandwich home to my grandson I truly appreciate those guy's the manager and all.
Loved the way they treated us and my daughters. Great customer service. 10 star review. Thank you!
Excellent food and great service

Quick and quality food with a short wait.

The staff have always been friendly and helpful.

Angel really stepped up and made a positive impact on my last visit as well. Definitely going to keep coming back
Large space with plenty of seating. Very quick service. Food is great. Wi-Fi is slow
This is the first time I've ever had a bad Panera experience. My lettuce was bitter, my sons pizza was cold and I had to ask twice for salad dressing

I used to love the Fuji apple salad at this location. I had to pay $12.79 for a salad that was all arugula and there's supposed to be four different blends. Will never go back because of that the employees have no idea how to make the food now.
Friendly staff. Clean facility. Good location. Just what you would expect from a Panera Bread.
Casual dining, also a place to just hang out in comfortable chairs. High quality food with healthy ingredients. Not cheap but you get what you pay for. Great soups here.
The place needs updating.  There were worn-out or dirty fixtures.  We had just coffee.
I feel under the weather  so I ordered chicken soup but I'm very disappointed mostly water and very salty, some noodles at the end. Honestly, Progresso soups are better.
Incredibly fast service, with generous servings
The food is good but the restaurant is a mess. It doesn't look like they have anyone cleaning the dining area. When you're paying $15+ for lunch, you expect more.

DO NOT ORDER CATERING ORDERS FROM THIS LOCATION.

Worst customer service and punctually. My order got delivered one hour AFTER. What's the point to order days before if for the day of, their excuse is that they are short on staff?! If clients place an order that your staff can't handle, it should be notified.

I called several times and they told me the order was on its way and this wasn't true.

Lack of professionalism. Terrible experience.
Great service when i picked up - the staff were helpful in making sure my order was complete, and even held the door on the way out!
Good healthy food
I haven't been to this location in a while, but when I come back there is roach on the floor. Gross. Not sure how clean they are back there. Won't be visiting this location again.
Very friendly and fast service.
Great pastries. Terrible sandwiches

I ordered my food with whom I assumed is a new employee. She had another employee standing near helping with questions. The cashier did a great job. When I received my Togo order the MOD took the recipe and checked through the bag to make sure everything was there. When I got home I unpacked my bag for my family and everything was there. Good Job everyone
First time eating Mac and Cheese, not bad, would have again.
Might as well have just ordered bread for $12. Absolutely no substance to the sandwich.
I love it
These are always nice places to relax and are laid back. I have the unlimited sips membership where you can't go wrong with it.

2 years ago I gave this place a four star review and have decided to remove that from this location. At 9:50 AM they are out of almost every single caffeinated drink and every single item with sausage, this is a supply chain management issue that Panera needs to address- now. This is happening at several locations, but usually only occurs after 3 pm. It's not even pass noon yet and they are already out of things.

View pictures as proof.

We had lunch catered from Panera Bread today and I enjoyed it. The ingredients were fresh and the roast beef was unique in color and taste. Not what I was expecting from a roast beef sandwich, but pleasantly surprised. The avocado was a nice touch. The cookie was outstanding and stood out for me. It was baked to perfection, extremely soft and chewy without being undercooked. I would probably try a different sandwich next time, but I would go back just for the cookies!
The food was delicious. The young lady that waited on us was very nice and upstanding. We had a large group  and she was very patient.
Great team workers as doordash driver I'm really happy! always fast service
I always love me a bowl of broccoli cheese soup and a turkey bravo sandwich
Ochen' vkusnye supy piure

Today I ordered a beef with carmalised onion sandwich and a chocolate pastry. That's the best sandwich they have in my opinion. I also like the French onion soup but didn't order it today. Panera Bread has been around for years because they offer tasty and healthy meals, nice ambiance and best pastries and bread!! And no I'm not a paid critique, I'm just a loyal customer for years!
Best quality, tasty and healthy lunch.
Best bread bowl
Good but very frequently out of bagels
Food was perfect.
Never disappointed.
Always great service. My order has always been accurate and delicious. I love this location.

The service was fast, the customer service was fair, but my latte was nasty. The young lady was apologetic and tried to fix it but it seems like they must've been trained incorrectly. The second time was equally as bland and tasteless. I paid $7.00 for milk and whipped cream. Never again.

I had an online order that I had an issue regarding delivery (issue was DoorDash, let's be honest). I called the store and spoke to Shelia, who was the manager on duty. She not only fixed the issue but went above and beyond to help me. Currently being at home with COVID, delivery was my only option.. and it was super frustrating having this issue. Thank you so much, Shelia, for taking great care of me - and the food was delicious!!

Enjoyed my first time in.   My wife always gets the Cinnamon crunch bagel and swears by it.  I ordered the Blueberry scone (delicious)  and a chocolate croissant for later... also tasty when re-heated. I'll return.

The food is almost always good but I would warn everyone that is planning on ordering ahead through the app that they almost never reserve their baked goods for you.

I've ordered bagels in the afternoon to pick up later in the day and pretty much every time, when I show up to pick up, they tell me they have sold out of the item that I bought several hours before. They also don't provide any kind of notification when they do sell out so you're kinda screwed.

I'm not sure if it's an issue with team communication at this location or if their app is not good at telling the store about orders ahead of time, but it's a serious issue that I hope they figure out soon.

Thank you to the young lady Isabela who despite being extremely busy at almost 8 p.m. on Friday, May 27th, acknowledged me right away when I walked up to the counter. There were 5 young workers behind the counter (I do realize they were all busy) however,  Isabela was the only one who acknowledged me right away and said she would be right with me. I didn't expect service right away and I was totally okay with waiting. I just appreciate being spoken to and not overlooked. I waited patiently. She helped me as soon as she could and was kind. My food was great. Thank you!
Incorrect order, and their online support is useless.  Wouldn't get delivery from here again.
Soup was warm not hot, the eat in area was in a bit of disarray..

Kiosk wouldn't take my gift card which was annoying! Never have baguettes available!! Tried Thai soup and it was horrible!!!  The quality of the soup was like getting a prepackage freezer item at the grocery store.  Stick to salads and sandwiches.  This place is priced way to high for average quality food imo.
I loved
Great food. Always enjoy eating here.
Excellent value for money
Great staff and consistent service.  You can find me here working all the time!
Deliciosa ensaladas.
Es un lugar para comer ligero. Muy agradable. Buena atencion
The loaves of ciabatta bread are smaller - the crease in the bag that allows it to expand doesnt even do so!

Saturday, March 26, 2022 I ordered $4 americano around 7pm. I was looking forward to having a nice cup of coffee with some warm Krispy Kreme donuts that I just purchased. However, I was very disappointed to receive a weak, almost watery, lukewarm to almost room temp cup of "coffee". In general I like Panera but on this occasion I would have been better off getting coffee from McDonalds.

Man where do I begin the young man that had dreads was so sweet he was a cashier I've never been there before and ask him suggestions and told him that I had a patient that had no teeth elderly what kind of soup would he recommend it's not too spicy he offered the soup and sandwich special I love the barbecue chicken sandwich my patient absolutely loves the broccoli and cheese and he just offered me different offers told me about the membership card which I still ain't activated sadly and I've been there like five times if he's there when I go in he automatically knows what I want to order or when I walk into pick up my order they all know who I am now but they're friendly faces and just wave and hey how are you know blah blah blah very super nice people and the first time I didn't know what to do besides after I order in the manager was out there explaining it to other people and he said here's my order thank you for coming and when I explained it was my first visit he's like welcome thank you for giving us a chance and I look forward to serving you again soon couldn't ask for anybody better to be running that place the staff is wonderful managers wonderful

My pickup order was late and on top of that, I decided to try the new chicken sandwich which tasted good but the presentation wasn't not that good. The sauce was all over the top of the bun instead of in the sandwich.
Fresh

I love Panera. The food quality is hard to mess up. So that was not the issue at all. I just have never been to a store where ever single staff member looked like they wanted to leave. They were under staffed for sure so that is a management issue. But sad employees bring the place down.

Nice place and food is always cooked well.  A little costly for anything other than breakfast.  Seating is plentiful and cozy.  The WiFi here always gives me trouble connecting and I have to use my hotspot (Panera places across the US vary widely with this issue).  I hate the parking at this particular place.  Most spots are for compact cars and regular parking feels smaller than normal.  You can park across the way in Target's parking lot for larger vehicles like pickup trucks.
Panera is a good place for eating and also just having coffee and pastry.
I highly recommend that chicken Mediterranean Bowl. Another favorite for our family is the turkey avocado sandwich. Outdoor seating is great.

Carina's customer service was extraordinary! She helped me understand the menu and helped me decide what I would get and it was delicious! She greeted me with a smiling face and a very warming welcome to Panera! Definitely will be back and I hope I am able to be served by Carina again!

Always a pleasure. Fresh products. Had a quick bite with a friend. Enjoyed Turkey Chili...just the right spice.

Wish their menus were clearer regarding $5.99 pick two.
Awesome spot for a business meeting
The food is excellent.

Love this location. Stopped in for my fav Greek Salad and also got the world famous broccoli cheese soup. On ckecking my order still in the store I was given a Cesar Salad and the order was corrected and I got a keep the Cesar Salad which I gave to my Son. The location always give GREAT service.

I was sorely disappointed when opening my order at work and both steak sandwiches were missing the signature sauce and one had a sliver of pickled onion.  It also would have been nice to have more than a slice of steak on the sandwich.  Very skimpy for the price.  Also the French Onion Soup I would not order again as it was just some broth with a few croutons to be put into it.  There really was no cheese except maybe a hint when you stirred it.  The French Onion soup I have eaten in the past was smothered with melted cheese on the top.  They really should not call this French Onion Soup.  It is broth with onions and throw a few croutons in.  It will be quite sometime before I order, if I do, from Panera's again.

Average, the coffee was tasting strange. The kitchen sink cookie had a "different" flavor to it. Yes I know it's 'whatever we had left' in the batter.... But maybe somethings shouldn't be mixed.  Not what my usual experience here is like. Usually pretty good . No so this time.  They must have been having a bad day. Everyone has a bad day once in awhile.
This is definitely one of our favorite locations! Always fresh and always fast!
It's good, service is fast, good is good
I love Panera but I always feel like they forget something
Best Panera Bread Restaurant Of All......
Ordered through app. Order said ready so I came in to pick it up and it wasn't ready. This happens frequently here but this time, the souffle I ordered had another 20 minutes to cook.
Your standard Panera Bread, they're all about the same. Nothing noteworthy to write home about. Panera is pricey for what it is sometimes, but solid every once in awhile.

The gentleman whose name was Kevin I believed made me the best strawberry banana smoothie I've ever had in my life no kippity cap. He also took my order with the nicest attitude and his service was quick. He even made sure to clean all the tables around us. Give that man a raise or something!
Love there order kiosks. I can actually enjoy lunch break without having to wait in line.
Great food.
As usual the quality is good. Nice and helpful staff. Food came out good.
Breakfast are fresh, bread made at place daily, good coffee and friendly people serving, costumer sometimes no obey law about required use of face mask when they are ordering food
Every Panera's I've been to, NC, Florida, and others provide the same quality of food and great service.

I've had good experiences going into the store to pick up food, but their curb side pickup is not reliable. I had to use this service when my toddler was sick to avoid exposing others to illness. It took over 15 minutes even after calling multiple times and having an employee hang up the phone. My baby started crying because of sitting in a still car and my sandwich's and soup were luke warm after delivery.
Very good flatbread pizza.  Service was excellent as well.
Owned by a greedy rich guy that likes to drop n bombs on the radio
Great coffee, great breakfast sandwich, love the atmosphere of the seating area, very comfy and great place to meet people to catch up
Food is great they really need to come down on the prices  Panera I am going to claim you on my taxes. I love Panera Bread
Coffee good

I do not see anything on your menus that I would eat. I really do not understand how you stay in business. I plant to never step foot in your property again. You desperately need to change your menu or go back to where you came from.
Enjoyed food and atmosphere!

I was in the store just before 11, and although not peak time, there seemed to be some delays in the kitchen. I ordered the egg sandwich with spinach and Avocado, the avocado was very hard, not even close to ripe. That was disappointing. The blueberry scone was wonderful, even better than expected. Green smoothie was also delicious, I appreciated having a non-dairy option.
Best asiago bagels!!
Delicious..
Staff was awesome, my to go meals were prepped quickly amd correctly, amd the food was great.

Stopped in for a quick lunch break. Decided to sit outside, despite warm temp. Had a bowl of the broccoli cheese soup and chicken salad sandwich with apple side. Soup very good, sandwich was passable, over $4 for what seems to be a quarter of a sandwich, is a bit steep. The miniature apple was not very tasty. Overpriced soup and sandwich place with fraction of a sandwich. Won't be doing this very often. Now I remember why it's been so long since we've been here last. Can't really recommend such a mediocre presentation.
The only fast food place anyone should be going to. Great  chemical free food, my favorite kind of bagels, and a bakery to boost!
Great food and service.
Worker dropped food on the floor, picked up the food and continued working. I informed the manager and the worker did not replace gloves, continued to make sandwiches.

Unfortunately wasn't able to completely enjoy my sandwich. Halfway down the freeway opened it to find it full of sauce and specifically said no sauce when placed order online so had to just eat the meat and cheese without the sauce on it.
Nice clean restaurant.  Food was excellent.
Panera is one of my favorite places. The cost is prohibitive though and the reason I don't go more often. Food always good. I was not thrilled to see that the kitchen staff doesn't wear masks .
Tried a new item, sandwich with BBQ chicken and cheese, generous portion, will have it again. Everything is in order here.
Nice atmosphere to work in.
Very friendly staff but the service was very slow.
Always delicious. The best place to eat healthy food
The food was good and server was friendly
Clean , great customer service!!
Excellent food and great service

Great customer service at this location. Stopped in for a quick breakfast and coffee and service was friendly and order accurate. Coffee was quite tasty. The wrap: bacon, tomato and egg was quite filling and yummy. It was nice to see they could also turn any sandwich into a wrap. This location is convenient and close to Novant Health-Matthews.
Me gusta su comida es bien suave para el estomago y esta buena
The food is great but it seems that they cut down the volume of salad and its not worth the price. The salads used to be huge.
We'll stop here quite often.  Primarily get a salad.   Bagels are very good. Pizza is ok.. yet it's not a pizza parlor,  so don't expect great pizza.  Good service.  I'd recommend.
Loved the pizza and salad .

I ordered on DoorDash and I saw my dasher was sitting there for about the last 40 minutes and the DoorDash lady who was really patient with them was told that Panera had "lost" the order. Judging by the other reviews they didn't even start making it yet or it was actually stolen from them because they weren't taking care of it. Either way they made the dasher wait another 25-30 minutes just to make the food again. It shows they didn't really care about the DoorDasher or the customer.

Order 30min ago.
I am checking manager, they not even start.
Just seating and talking....
This place used so good. Now, they make enough money. They don't care customer.
Been waiting 40 minutes for my food and they still don't have record of it but my card has been charged. At this rate I'm going to miss my class. Not a great experience tbh :(
Great Customer service. Always enjoyed it!!
Always good

I was having a craving for Panera but I have had nothing but bad experiences no matter which one I went to- I was out on 485 and decided that I would stop at the Panera Bread in Matthews - I pulled up and the parking lot was full (good sign maybe) - so I made my way inside and before I could even reach the door there is this girl (later found out her name was Anna) she had her hands full as she was doing curbside pickup - However with her hands full she stopped, held the door for me and said hello and asked how my day was!! All while smiling a big smile that you could see underneath her mask!!  I went inside and placed my order- I watched as Anna continued to work just as fast as she could- still polite and still smiling- I then received my food, a Chipotle Chicken Avacodo sandwich which a was phenomenal!! I had never had one that wasn't super dry until this day!! It was delicious!! I have to say that this is  HANDS DOWN THE BEST PANERA IN A 30 MILE RADIUS!! I will be back and all of you should give them a try as well!! I promise you will not be disappointed!! Again- Thanks Anna for being who you are!! :)
Delicious bagels.  Fast, friendly service.

I go to this place 4+ times a week and the customer service is excellent sometimes and others times they are rude couple times I should to wait over 15 minutes for coffee and they look at me  standing in front of the counter and no even paid attention

We love Panera food, but they never get the orders correct. First with delivery, then even with picking up in the store. I have lost a ton of money due to missing items. This store is constantly messing up orders.
Great service.  Friendly staff.
This place always has great food
People are great sometimes the system does not report I am there properly.
Good outdoor seating
Typical excellence service anh food
Great place for coffee and food.

I never leave reviews, however, I must say Andres really is the best. He is usually the one to deliver my food and he always has the best attitude. He smiles, makes sure to ask if the food is ok and if the order is correct before he leaves, and always seems to love his job! He is the nicest worker I had ever stumbled upon. If Andres is the one to deliver your food, know you received the best! Thank you for your kindness Andres!!

We ordered ahead (flatbread pizza), they must have made our order hours ahead as there was no warmth to that pizza at all. It was very tasteless and didn't satisfy my taste for pizza or even a decent flatbread. Extremely lacking in toppings or spices. Would not recommend.
Good food.

Great service! One time, they messed up my order and forgot a whole sandwich. I called to let them know and that I wasn't able to come get the missing item as my lunch break was over. They delivered the missing sandwich to my job for free. Definitely recommend!
Friendly staff and delicious food. Always excited to visit this place.
Cold coffee
Fresh baked goodies all the time.

Horrible delivery. The last few times we were missing items but no big deal they came out and redid the delivery.  This time though the order didn't arrive to my door, there are 3 people in the house and the driver claimed he knocked. Didn't hear a knock. We get delivery all the time so we are quick and prompt with answering the door. The driver argued with me, had an attitude, when I told him it didn't arrive. I even checked others doors to see if it was at the wrong door. I didn't see it. I asked for a refund and he still got snarky about the refund. I had to ask for a confirmation on cancelation cause I didn't trust him. He ended up putting someone else on the phone to handle his mistake.
The best

Order food to-go during this virus time!    This is a good Panera. At lunch time it gets a little crowded,  but everything they have is good.   Limited parking in front. Lots of parking nearby.  M has given all his restaurant reviews a single star.  You might want to ignore that review.  B's 2-stars are for delivery.
Very clean and friendly. Very nice flatbread pizza on special today
I love the salads but why is the bread so hard? I could use it to club someone into unconsciousness.
Quick friendly service. Establishment has an "A" rating and the food is really good.
Margherita pizza was great! Being vegetarian it is hard to find things to eat out. Also my daughter loved the broccoli mac and cheese. Keep up the good work Panera.
Nice place.
Love it the bread and desert there Is awesome love going there
Fast and friendly service and the food was great.
Ask for Tom P! Good guy!
Good
Its a Panera not much to say.. you know what to expect.  The food is over priced and blah here.

The staff were inviting and friendly and the food was amazing. The only place I've ever had a sourdough bread bowl was 15 years ago in California.  The only complaint I have is that they didn't have clam chowder.  Please consider adding this and I will be happier than I ever have been ^^ I love Panera Bread.
Over priced.Soup was not hot. Salad was very fesh.We sat outside to eat. Service was quick.
The person taking our order knew the menu well. Food was very good!
The order was not right but they fixed it.
I love panera. It was delicious  clean n the staff was great. Thank you. Looking forward for my rewards.

Vegetarians and people with allergies beware. Not for the first time I found bits if chicken in my said where I requested no chicken. Luckily, I spotted them before eating the salad so threw it away. Really wish your staff would be more careful.
Dining in may be a fine experience, but the last two delivery orders placed were both incomplete and incorrect. The quality control on delivery orders appears to be lacking.
Nice convenience

Had an excellent experience here. The most professional, friendly employees helped me place an order (it's been a couple of years since I've eaten at a Panera Bread!), plus recover my old Panera account.
